<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="89" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="89">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="89">
The new species belongs to the 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Banks" baseAuthorityYear="1913" class="Insecta" family="Coniopterygidae" genus="Heteroconis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Heteroconis terminalis" order="Neuroptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="89" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="terminalis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="89">Heteroconis terminalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group sensu 
<bibRefCitation author="Sziraki, Gy" journalOrPublisher="Folia Entomologica Hungarica" pageId="0" pageNumber="89" pagination="101 - 136" refId="B11" refString="Sziraki, Gy, 2005. Species grouping of several genera and subgenera of Coniopterygidae. Folia Entomologica Hungarica 66: 101 - 136" title="Species grouping of several genera and subgenera of Coniopterygidae." volume="66" year="2005">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Sziráki">Sziraki</normalizedToken>
(2005)
</bibRefCitation>
. The male genitalia suggest a relationship with 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Banks" baseAuthorityYear="1913" class="Insecta" family="Coniopterygidae" genus="Heteroconis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Heteroconis terminalis" order="Neuroptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="89" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="terminalis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="89">Heteroconis terminalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. However, the new species is characterized by the presence of a median projection on the male frons between the antennae, which is absent in 
<taxonomicName genus="H." lsidName="H. terminalis" pageId="0" pageNumber="89" rank="species" species="terminalis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="89">H. terminalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The two apical flagellomeres are whitish in the new species, whereas only the apical one is whitish in 
<taxonomicName genus="H." lsidName="H. terminalis" pageId="0" pageNumber="89" rank="species" species="terminalis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="89">H. terminalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Stylus about 3-times as long as wide in the new species, about 5-times as long as wide in 
<taxonomicName genus="H." lsidName="H. terminalis" pageId="0" pageNumber="89" rank="species" species="terminalis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="89">H. terminalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Zhao &amp; Sziráki &amp; Liu" authorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Coniopterygidae" genus="Heteroconis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Heteroconis yunnanensis" order="Neuroptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="89" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="yunnanensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="89">Heteroconis yunnanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. is distinguished by having the last two flagellomeres whitish, by the presence of a median projection between the antennae, by flagellomeres 3 and 4 with a short spine, and by stylus about 3 times as long as wide in lateral view.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
